==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corymb
<hw>Cor"ymb</hw> <pr>(k?r"?mb ⟦or⟧ -?m; 220)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>corymbus</ets> cluster of flowers, Gr.
<grk>ko`rymbos</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
flat-topped or convex cluster of flowers, each on its own footstalk, and
arising from different points of a common axis, the outermost blossoms
expanding first, as in the hawthorn.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any
flattish flower cluster, whatever be the order of blooming, or a similar
shaped cluster of fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corymbed</ent>⟦br⟧
